<p>Berlitz International is a premier language learning company, operating over 450 learning centers in over 60 countries. With worldwide headquarters in Princeton, NJ, Berlitz has been providing effective and innovative language learning services to a wide range of customers since 1878.
<p>In 2003, Berlitz undertook significant upgrading of their marketing to Internet customers. A key part of this strategy involved attracting and guiding potential customers with an engaging web-based course recommendation system. The goal was to personalize Berlitzĺ offerings both to the wants of each web site visitor and varied offerings in each metropolitan area and language, thereby increasing the rate visitors would follow-up by enrolling in a course.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>Berlitz turned to Nevo to realize their vision for the Global Course Advisor (GCA).
Berlitz wanted GCA to offer a custom experience to each site visitor from around the
world depending on many factors, including the visitorĺs choice of language in which
to view the site, and tailoring the session to the visitorĺs answers to other survey
questions. Based on visitor responses, GCA would identify the Berlitz language courses
that best fit the visitorĺs preferences and offer easy ways for the visitor to take
the next step toward enrolling in a course. GCA offers a simple and short survey and recommendation experience to each visitor, while preserving extensive flexibility to
present automatically very different experiences to different users and change the
visitor experiences over time.
<p>Berlitz also wanted its marketing and learning center staff around the world to
control and revise the experience GCA presents to their prospective customers. GCA
needed to provide simple and intuitive construction tools that allow flexibility
while guiding the user to ensure a presentable result.


<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>The GCA solution integrates the following five major components.
<ol class="listText">

<li>Customer-facing GCA web front end implemented using ASP.NET. The resulting web
site is highly customizable through the administrative back end, enabling control
over page content, page sequencing, automatic language translation, and custom-defined
navigation based on visitor inputs.
</li><li>GCA database implemented in SQL Server 2000.
</li><li>Recommendation engine implementing a tunable optimization algorithm to
select courses that best fit visitorĺs declared preferences, implemented in C#
in the .NET framework. The algorithm produces a discrete ordering of the choices
and selects the best scoring choices to present to the site visitor.
</li><li>Web site building and administrative back end to enable Berlitz marketing
staff members, subject to access and authorization controls, to tailor each of
the web site experiences associated with different sets of input parameters.
For example, the web site experience for a child seeking an English language
course in Germany may be completely different from the web site experience for
an adult seeking instruction in French at a learning center in the United States.
</li><li>The existing Berlitz worldwide database holding the catalog of Berlitz
course offerings.
</li></ol>
Nevo worked collaboratively with Berlitz to develop specifications and interfaces
for these components and then designed and implemented GCA


